12/7/00
  Overnight test result:
    - 9 channel grooming: reset twice due to mux fail.
    - single channel auto switching: DPI reset once due to stack overflow in
      SpliceReq tesk.

  Check in: Revert back to ver 3.01 C6x compiler  (1116.fls)
  Check in: Audio time base adjustment to solve the lips sync problem
      We noticed that the output is out of lips sync first time the code
      starts up, but ok after successive re-apply.  The reason is that
      prev tbOffset is uninitialized at the first start up, caussing
      tbJumpAdj() to be called.  Unfortunately, we did not adjust audio
      time base offset.  Hence out of lips sync at first start up.
      At successive re-apply, the prevTbOffset is initialized and hence
      no TB jump is detected.

  The throttle branch is called rel2_2dp_throttle.

